					<h3>1. User Consent</h3>
					<p>941Digital respects your privacy rights and is committed to protect the Personal Information of its users. We take a variety of physical, technical, and administrative measures to protect your information from disclosure to or access by third parties.
					</p>
					<p>By submitting your Personal Information through our Site or Services, you explicitly agree to the use, disclosure, and collection of your Information as per this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Policy, your choice is not to use 941Digital.
					</p>
					<p>This Policy explains our privacy practices of the Site and Services provided by 941Digital. By accessing or utilizing 941Digital.com, you accept this Policy including our data collection, processing, disclosure, use and retention of your Personal Information. This Policy may change every once in a while and on the off chance that there are any material changes to how your own data is utilized, We will notify you. Your continued use of the Site, after Site and Policy updates, is considered to be an acknowledgment of those updates, so please check the Policy periodically.
					</p>
					<h3>2. Children's Privacy</h3>
					<p>Our Service isn't offered to people younger than 16 (or the legal age in your jurisdiction) so, If you are under 16 years of age, then please do not use or access the Site and/or Services in any manner. We don't purposefully accumulate Personal Information from visitors who are younger than 16. If We learn that Personal Data has been collected on the Site and/or Services from persons under 16 years of age (without verifiable parental consent), then We will take appropriate steps to remove necessary information or if you are a parent (or a legal guardian) of a child, and you discover that We might have the information (such as name, address, telephone number, or e-mail address) of a child, then please Contact Us at legal@941Digital.com with appropriate details, and We will delete that information promptly.
					</p>
					<h3>3. Information We Collect
					</h3>
					<h3>a. Information You Give to Us</h3>
					<h3>I. Personal Information</h3>
					<p>We ask for, collect and store Personal Information (data that allows someone to identify or contact you) about you, such as your name, e-mail, phone number, location, Skype and Hangout IDs when you Contact Us, Submit Project Requirement or your details on our website, register to the Site, place the order, purchase or opt for any of our Service(s).
					</p>
					<p>In general, at your discretion, you can browse the Website without telling us who you are or revealing any personal information about yourself. However, once you give us your personal information, you are not anonymous to us.
					</p>
					<p>If you Contact Us via e-mail or provide Us feedback about our services, We will collect your name, e-mail address, as well as any other content included in the e-mail, in order to send you a reply.
					</p>
					<p>If you rate our services, We may collect your name, e-mail address, your photo, your designation, your location, your website URL, business name, and your review description in order to display it in our portfolio.
					</p>
					<h3>II. Payment Information</h3>
					<p>When you place an order or make a purchase, either you will be redirected to our 3rd party payment processors, or we will allow our payment
