					<p>Your Privacy is essential for 941Digital, and We are committed to protect your Personal Information. We are continuously implementing and updating administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your Personal Information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. When you enter sensitive information on our forms, We (or our third party service providers) encrypt transmission of that information using secure socket layer technology (SSL). However, please note that no technique for web transmission or storage is 100 % secure, so 941Digital cannot guarantee its absolute security. Additionally, take note of that We may hold and store your data in our databases even after your 941Digital record is deactivated as long as We have a legitimate reason to do so.
